<exercise id="fs-idm379755296">
<problem id="fs-idm373368528">
<para id="fs-idm373368272"><link class="lo-reference" document="m67840"/>The following historical information is from Assisi Community Markets.</para>
<media id="fs-idm342530448" alt="Year 1 42,000, 12,500, 6,200, 12,500, 3,200. Year 2 37,500, 16,800, 7,600, 14,600, 3,700. Year 3 26,800, 22,900, 10,300, 19,800, 4,500. Year 4 22,100, 28,000, 15,400, 20,600, 6,000. Year 5 15,700, 29,500, 16,700, 22,900, 8,200.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/OSX_Acct_F02_03_TP02_img.jpg"/>
</media>
<para id="fs-idm344754512">Calculate the working capital and current ratio for each year. What observations do you make, and what actions might the owner consider taking?</para>
</problem>
